==Korean==

===Etymology===

===Adjective===
'''굽다''' (gubda, gupda)
#to be [[bent]], [[curved]], [[humped]], [[hunched]]

====Derived terms====
*굽실[[거리]]다 (gubsil-georida) to [[bow]] the neck repeatedly, [[humble]] oneself 
*굽어[[보]]다 (gubEo-boda) to look down and [[pay attention]] 
*굽어[[살피]]다 (gubEo-salpida) to look down and [[pay attention]]
*굽은 (gubEun) [[bent]], [[curved]], [[humped]], [[humpbacked]], [[hunched]] 
*굽이 (gub-i) [[bend]], [[curve]], [[turn]] 
*굽히다 (gubhida) to [[bend]], [[curve]], [[hunch]]

====Related terms====
*[[고부라]][[지]]다 (gobura-jida) to be [[bent]], [[curved]], [[humped]], [[humpbacked]], [[hunched]] (to a lesser degree than 구부러지다 (gubureo-jida))
*[[곱]]다 (gobda) to be [[bent]], [[curved]], [[hunched]]
*[[곱사]][[등]][[이]] (gobsa-deung-i) [[humpback]], [[hunchback]]
*[[꼽]]다 (kkobda) to [[bend]] (the finger), [[count]]
*[[꼽추]] (kkobchu) [[humpback]], [[hunchback]]
*[[구루]][[병]] (guru-byeong) [[kyphosis]] (from Greek ''kyphos'' "[[humpbacked]]" cognate with ''kybos'' "[[vertebra]], [[cube]]")
*[[구르]]다 (gureuda) to [[roll]]
*[[구리]] (guri) [[copper]]
*[[구부리]]다 (guburida) to [[bend]], [[curve]], [[hump]], [[hunch]]
*[[구부러]][[지]]다 (gubureo-jida) to be [[bent]], [[curved]], [[humped]], [[humpbacked]], [[hunched]]
*[[구불]][[거리]]다 (gubul-georida) to [[meander]], [[wind]], [[zigzag]] 
*[[혹]] (hog) [[bump]], [[hump]]

===Noun===
'''굽''' (gub, gup)
#[[hoof]] (as of horses and cows) 
#[[heel]] (as of shoes) 
#[[foot]] (as of bowels) 

====Derived terms====
*[[말]]굽 (mal-gub) [[horse]] [[hoof]], [[horseshoe]] 

===Verb===
'''굽다''' (gubda, gupda)

#[[bake]], [[broil]], [[roast]]  
#[[overlap]] (the two or more marks, called [[말]] (''mal'', literally ''horse''), running on the [[w:Yot|Yut]] ([[윷]]) board so that they can run together, hence multiply faster.) 

====Derived terms====
*구운 (guun) baked, roasted 
*구워[[먹]]다 (guwo-meogda) roast and eat

